lead_paragraph: Eugenie Bouchard slumped to a first-round defeat at the U.S. Open on Tuesday but the Canadian might yet leave Flushing Meadows a big winner with her lawsuit against the grand slam and United States Tennis Association still to hit the courts.

headline.print_headline: Bouchard Falls at U.S. Open but Legal Battle Continues
